shrine /ʃraɪn/

(shrines) 

1. N-COUNT A shrine is a place of worship which is associated with a particular holy person or object. 圣殿 

例： ...the holy shrine of Mecca. …麦加的圣殿。 

2. N-COUNT A shrine is a place that people visit and treat with respect because it is connected with a dead person or with dead people that they want to remember. 圣地 

例： The monument has been turned into a shrine to the dead and the missing. 这座纪念碑已经变成了纪念那些过世或失踪的人的圣地。

